  "texts": [
    "Let (M 1, g 1) (resp.",
    "(M 2, g 2)) be a Ricci soliton obtained from a solution (ǧ 1, ρ 1, h 1) (resp.",
    "(ǧ 2, ρ 2, h 2)) of the twisted harmonic-Einstein equation as in Proposition 3.4.",
    "Then, there exists an isometric bundle map between (M 1, g 1) and (M 2, g 2) if and only if (ǧ 1, ρ 1, h 1) is equivalent to (ǧ 2, ρ 2, h 2).Proof.",
    "By Proposition 2.15, an isometric bundle map between (M 1, g 1) and (M 2, g 2) is equivalently described by an isometry f: (B 1, ǧ1) → (B 2, ǧ2) and a Lie algebra bundle isomorphism f ad: adM 1 → adM 2 such thath 1 = f * ad h 2, ∇ ad,1 = f * ad ∇ ad,2."
